    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <head>No. 848.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 11, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 7th instant, concerning the fine imposed by the customs
                    authorities at San Diego, California, upon the Mexican vessel <hi rend="italic"
                        >Monserrat</hi>, on account of a defect in her papers, stated to have been
                    duly authenticated, but accidentally lost by the capsizing of a small boat to
                    which they had been transferred.</p>
                <p>In reply I desire to say that a copy of your note has been sent to the Secretary
                    of the Treasury for the consideration of his Department.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
